\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces  The top 50 genes ranked by the gene score. The score of gene \(g\) is \(1 - \mathrm  {ECDF}_g(0.9)\), the fraction of individuals \(i\) for which \(S_{ig}>0.9\) and is indicated by the length of dark blue, dark green or dark red bars. Note that the same ranking and score is shown in the bottom half of Fig.\nobreakspace  {}2\hbox {}. The right border of the light blue, light green and light red bars is at \(1 - \mathrm  {ECDF}_g(0.8)\). The length of the black bars indicates the fraction of individuals passing the test of nearly unbiased expression (Eq.\nobreakspace  {}2\hbox {}). ``X'' characters next to gene names indicate reference allele bias, while ``0'' indicate that reference allele bias could not be determined due to small amount of data. }}{16}}
